Introduction

Mina (미나) is a South Korean singer, rapper, and actress under Jellyfish Entertainment. She is a former member of the girl group gugudan, its sub-units gugudan SEMINA and OGUOGU, and the project girl group I.O.I.

On December 30, 2020, Jellyfish Entertainment announced gugudan would disband on December 31 after four years together.

She made her acting debut in the MBC romantic comedy series Children of the 20th Century in 2017, acting as the younger counterpart of Han Ye-seul.
